cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO. 

The paper deals with visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel method that combines part-based tracking and support vector machines, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions the speed and robustness of the proposed method, which suggests that it may fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.RO (Robotics).
